h, because it is often convenient or even necessary in a modern English-dominated world (especially so close to England).%0a%3c %0a%3c We can debate and debate, but at the end of the day, why does this really matter? Whether Welsh is endangered or not, there is still no harm in trying to preserve a language that is potentially losing its place. While globalization is probably a large factor in the popularity of Welsh declining, it also adds an avenue for Welsh speakers to talk about their language, organize ways to preserve it, and even work with multiple languages at the same time.%0a%3c %0a%3c So while we may not be able to conclude whether Welsh is endangered or not, there is still plenty we can do to keep it alive and flourishing.%0a%3c %0a%3c Sources:%0a%3c https://repozytorium.ukw.edu.pl/bitstream/handle/item/5119/Is%2520Welsh%2520an%2520Endangered%2520Language.pdf?sequence=1&isAllowed=y#:~:text=IS%2520WELSH%2520AN%2520ENDANGERED%2520LANGUAGE%253F,-Introduction&text=makes%2520linguists%2520consider%2520Welsh%2520a,classified%2520as%2520an%2520endangered%2520language.%0a%3c https://www.cnn.com/2019/04/09/asia/endangered-languages-welsh-hawaiian-cantonese-intl%0a%3c https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2013/aug/12/welsh-language-extinction-use%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Expansions:%0a%3c [[#expansions]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#expansionsend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%3c %0a%3c (:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:elseif [ equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:andrewid} '' || equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:section} '' ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c You must enter your andrew ID and section before submitting an expansion. %0a%3c %0a%3c (:else:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Comments%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c (:if equal {$Author} {$:Author}:)